{"title":"Tonal instrument","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Tonal_instrument","type":"markdown","data":"In *[NetHack](/wiki/NetHack \"NetHack\")*, **tonal instruments** are [instruments](/wiki/Instrument \"Instrument\") which can be used to play a particular melody, including the [passtune](/wiki/Passtune \"Passtune\") if you know it.\n\n[ ]\n\n## Contents\n\n- [1 List of tonal instruments](#List_of_tonal_instruments)\n- [2 Description](#Description)\n- [3 Strategy](#Strategy)\n- [4 Messages](#Messages)\n- [5 References](#References)\n\n## List of tonal instruments\n\nThe tonal instruments are:\n\n- [wooden flute](/wiki/Wooden_flute \"Wooden flute\")\n- [magic flute](/wiki/Magic_flute \"Magic flute\")\n- [tooled horn](/wiki/Tooled_horn \"Tooled horn\")\n- [frost horn](/wiki/Frost_horn \"Frost horn\")\n- [fire horn](/wiki/Fire_horn \"Fire horn\")\n- [wooden harp](/wiki/Wooden_harp \"Wooden harp\")\n- [magic harp](/wiki/Magic_harp \"Magic harp\")\n- [bugle](/wiki/Bugle \"Bugle\")\n\n## Description\n\nApplying a tonal instrument will prompt you if you want to improvise; pressing [n](/wiki/N \"N\") will instead allow you to select a series of five notes from A-G to play. If you are [stunned](/wiki/Stun \"Stun\"), [confused](/wiki/Confused \"Confused\"), or [hallucinating](/wiki/Hallucinating \"Hallucinating\"), you will improvise automatically with the tonal instrument.[\\[1\\]](#cite_note-1)\n\n## Strategy\n\nTonal instruments are the only ones that can be used to play and uncover the passtune.\n\n## Messages\n\n- You extract a strange sound from the \\<instrument>!\n\n  You successfully played a melody on a tonal instrument.\n\n## References\n\n1. [↑](#cite_ref-1) [src/music.c in NetHack 3.6.7, line 700](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.7_Released/src/music.c#L700)\n\n[![This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.7. Click here for more information.](/images/f/f7/Nh367-icon.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.7. Click here for more information.\")\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Tonal instrument - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Tonal_instrument\",\"wgTitle\":\"Tonal instrument\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":151434,\"wgRevisionId\":151434,\"wgArticleId\":9231,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"Nethack-367 articles\",\"Musical instruments\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPageContentModel\":\"wikitext\",\"wgSeparatorTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDigitTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDefaultDateFormat\":\"dmy\",\"wgMonthNames\":[\"\",\"January\",\"February\",\"March\",\"April\",\"May\",\"June\",\"July\",\"August\",\"September\",\"October\",\"November\",\"December\"],\"wgMonthNamesShort\":[\"\",\"Jan\",\"Feb\",\"Mar\",\"Apr\",\"May\",\"Jun\",\"Jul\",\"Aug\",\"Sep\",\"Oct\",\"Nov\",\"Dec\"],\"wgRelevantPageName\":\"Tonal_instrument\",\"wgRelevantArticleId\":9231,\"wgRequestId\":\"9b39c175923473fe62949f49\",\"wgCSPNonce\":false,\"wgIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRelevantPageIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRestrictionEdit\":[],\"wgRestrictionMove\":[],\"wgWikiEditorEnabledModules\":[],\"wgCategoryTreePageCategoryOptions\":\"{\\\"mode\\\":0,\\\"hideprefix\\\":20,\\\"showcount\\\":true,\\\"namespaces\\\":false}\"});mw.loader.state({\"site.styles\":\"ready\",\"noscript\":\"ready\",\"user.styles\":\"ready\",\"user\":\"ready\",\"user.options\":\"ready\",\"user.tokens\":\"loading\",\"ext.cite.styles\":\"ready\",\"mediawiki.legacy.shared\":